{"name": "siphash24", "metadata": {"name": "siphash24", "version": "1.7", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v2 or later (LGPLv2+)", "Programming Language :: C", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://dnicolodi.github.io/python-siphash24/", "dependencies": [], "summary": "Streaming-capable SipHash-1-3 and SipHash-2-4 Implementation", "upload_time": 1728999711}, "documentation": ["% SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Daniele Nicolodi <daniele@grinta.net>\n\n% SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 OR LGPL-2.1-or-later\n\n# siphash24: Streaming-capable SipHash Implementation\n\nThis module provides a C-based implementation of [SipHash](https://cr.yp.to/siphash/siphash-20120918.pdf) with an\ninterface compatible with the hash functions provided by the\n[hashlib](https://docs.python.org/3/library/hashlib.html) standard library module. SipHash-1-3 and SipHash-2-4\nvariants are currently implemented. The module [documentation](https://dnicolodi.github.io/python-siphash24/)\nprovides a detailed description of the API.\n\nThis module differs from other similar modules by providing a\nstreaming-capable implementation and an interface compatible to the\nhash functions provided by the `hashlib` standard library module and\nby providing binary wheels for all supported Python releases on the\nmost common platforms. More platforms can be added to the build job\nas needed.\n\nFollowing the `hashlib` interface, the return value of the\n`digest()` method is a `bytes` object. SipHash values are\ncustomarily stored as 64-bit integers. This module extends the\n`hashlib` interface with an additional `intdigest()` method that\nreturns the hash values as a 64-bit signed int object.\n\nThis module is implemented as a thin [Cython](https://cython.org/)-based wrapper around a\nC language SipHash implementation copied, with minimal modifications\nto allow compilation with MSCV, from the [c-siphash library](https://github.com/c-util/c-siphash) by\nDavid Rheinsberg and co-authors. The c-siphash library is based on\nthe SipHash [reference implementation](https://github.com/veorq/SipHash) by Jean-Philippe Aumasson and\nDaniel J. Bernstein released to the Public Domain. This module is\ndistributed with the same license as the c-siphash library:\n[Apache-2.0](https://spdx.org/licenses/Apache-2.0.html) or [LGPL-2.1-or-later](https://spdx.org/licenses/LGPL-2.1-or-later.html).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "docs.conf", "documentation": ["SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Daniele Nicolodi <daniele@grinta.net>", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 OR LGPL-2.1-or-later"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "docs.conf.path", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.pyproject", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.project", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.copyright", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.author", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.language", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.html_theme", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.html_title", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.extensions", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "docs.conf.intersphinx_mapping", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "check", "documentation": ["SPDX-FileCopyrigh